item.title: I'm a coin collector - the exact details you have to look for to find a 2022 Lincoln penny worth up
item.description: WHILE most rare US coins were minted in the 18th, 19th, or 20th century, there are some pieces minted this year that carry value. Coin collectors have noticed that certain 2022 Lincoln pennies bear signs of a "die clash" error, meaning they could be worth more than $100 in an auction. Dies are the metal pieces used to strike blank coin planchets and leave images engraved on them. Clash errors occur when heads and tails dies collide with one another without a blank coin in between, damaging one or both dies.
